<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>i3 FAQ - Individual question feed</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/questions/</link><description>Frequently asked questions and answers about the i3 window manager</description><atom:link href="http://faq.i3wm.org/feeds/question/854/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright i3, 2012</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 23 Dec 2012 21:02:47 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>How to force status bar update</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/854/how-to-force-status-bar-update/</link><description>I have commands in my .i3/config like

    bindsym XF86AudioRaiseVolume exec amixer set Master 2+

My i3status displays current volume in percents, but I have to wait the inteval (1 second in my case) for the bar to update so I can see the current volume. Is there a way to force refresh of the status bar, so it'll update as soon as I set the volume?</description><pubDate>Wed, 05 Dec 2012 11:30:09 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/854/how-to-force-status-bar-update/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Michael for &lt;p&gt;I have commands in my .i3/config like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;bindsym XF86AudioRaiseVolume exec amixer set Master 2+
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My i3status displays current volume in percents, but I have to wait the inteval (1 second in my case) for the bar to update so I can see the current volume. Is there a way to force refresh of the status bar, so it'll update as soon as I set the volume?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/854/how-to-force-status-bar-update/?answer=859#post-id-859</link><description>Starting with commit http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3status/commit/?id=0a608d4af67fe59390f2e8931f61b664f48660db, you can use `killall -USR1 i3status` ;-).</description><pubDate>Wed, 05 Dec 2012 16:51:19 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/854/how-to-force-status-bar-update/?answer=859#post-id-859</guid></item><item><title>Comment by nullsub for &lt;p&gt;Starting with commit &lt;a href="http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3status/commit/?id=0a608d4af67fe59390f2e8931f61b664f48660db"&gt;http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3statu...&lt;/a&gt;, you can use &lt;code&gt;killall -USR1 i3status&lt;/code&gt; ;-).&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/854/how-to-force-status-bar-update/?comment=931#comment-931</link><description>Nice. I am waiting for the next version which includes this.</description><pubDate>Sun, 23 Dec 2012 21:02:47 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/854/how-to-force-status-bar-update/?comment=931#comment-931</guid></item><item><title>Comment by ttjjss for &lt;p&gt;Starting with commit &lt;a href="http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3status/commit/?id=0a608d4af67fe59390f2e8931f61b664f48660db"&gt;http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3statu...&lt;/a&gt;, you can use &lt;code&gt;killall -USR1 i3status&lt;/code&gt; ;-).&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/854/how-to-force-status-bar-update/?comment=861#comment-861</link><description>Wow, you rock. Thank you!</description><pubDate>Wed, 05 Dec 2012 17:32:54 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/854/how-to-force-status-bar-update/?comment=861#comment-861</guid></item></channel></rss>